      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BEST EAGLE (1) was solid fresh then improved sharply at Kilcoy over 1500m when runner-up. Fitter again and blinkers added. Should take catching this longer journey. GENERAL GORDON (2) resumed for a new yard over 1420m at Grafton in heavy ground and wasn't beaten far. Fitter for the longer trip and expected to be in the finish. ARGYLE GOLD (3) wasn't too far away over 1400m on the Sunny Coast last time and is suited here. Yet to place in six starts but five have been in richer company and drawn to sit with a trial and run on hard. One of the chances. FROSTY'S GOTCHA (6) is long overdue and can run another good race.",
